Author-Name:   Moon, Youngme
Title: 
 Intimate Exchanges: Using Computers to Elicit Self-Disclosure from Consumers.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 323-39
Issue: 4
Volume: 26
Year: 2000
Month:  March 
Abstract:

 This investigation examines the dynamics associated with soliciting
 intimate information from consumers via computers. Experiment 1 identifies
 two factors--reciprocity and sequence--that affect the likelihood that
 people will reveal intimate information about themselves via a computer.
 Experiment 2 provides evidence that intimate information exchanges can
 affect how consumers behave in subsequent interactions. Implications for
 marketing research and practice are discussed.


