Author-Name:   Zaltman, Gerald
Title: 
 Consumer Researchers: Take a Hike!

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 423-28
Issue: 4
Volume: 26
Year: 2000
Month:  March 
Abstract:

 Consumer research needs broader intellectual peripheral vision. This
 requires learning to see relevance in seemingly distant fields and taking
 ignorance as a friend. A particularly challenging but highly relevant
 topic concerns the (un)conscious mind and the essential unity of body,
 brain, mind, and society. The two books discussed here are exciting
 journeys into the biology of the (un)conscious mind and how it is
 ultimately shaped by society.


